               <msContents>
                  <summary>F<locus target="#2r">fols. 2r, </locus>-63r: Lectionary for the Church Year, አስልጥ ዘሌሊት, arranged for the church year with red ink in the upper margin. <locus target="#1v">1v, </locus>: pen trials using the trinitiarian formula and other text. F<locus target="#4v">4v, </locus> and ff., mentions the owner ገብረ መድኀን. <locus target="#63r">63r, </locus> has a record of ownership and gifting: "This book belongs to Däjaz[mač] ማኅራይ who bought it with his own money and gave it to [the church of] Dabra Sellasie." Following is an excerpt from the Gospel of John. <locus target="#63v">63v</locus>: Excerpt from the Prayer for Saturday from the Horologium for the Night Hours of Abba Giyorgis, written in red ink.</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                     <textLang/>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
